<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO DOC SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Fri May 30 22:08:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Spatz:<br><br>
&gt;&quot;You don't need a high school dipoma from Nurse Ratchet to<br>
know the obvious, that money rules the world. Always has, always will. Art, put away your metaphysical onion, but hang on tight to your wallet.&quot;&lt;<br><br>
I do not wish to get in between the connection &quot;thing&quot; you have for Nurse Rachet, but I do not appreciate the glib manner in which you attempt to invalidate my thoughts on the matter. To many NamVets, &quot;...to know the obvious&quot; is an insult of the highest order. What feels like &quot;original&quot; thought to us can be at times the result of long and very painful exploration. It might surprise you that many of us have to start over at the beginning in many areas of thought and behavior to just begin to &quot;come home&quot; in a manner recognizable to the rest of the world.<br><br>
I do not care if you disagree, and I welcome a debate, but do not try to come across as a self styled expert who is going to tell me what to think and feel.<br><br>
In this case, my thoughts were NOT obvious to me until I worked them through. Furthermore, I have an emotional response toward the opressed Vietnamese people and the raw deal they continue to get from all sides. I remember all too well what I did in the name of their freedom, and the abysmal failure of the whole mess. That continues to hurt.<br><br>
That is what my post was all about. Feelings. Do you have any?<br><br>
Go play with Nurse Ratchet if you wish, but stay out of my mind.<br><br>

